title: For Sale:  M6 Scout Survival Rifle (.22 lr over .410 shotgun)
postcontent:
The M6 Scout is a multipurpose, survival firearm, combining an over/under rifle (.22 long rifle) and a shotgun (.410 bore).  The M6 design and model number come from the M6 Aircrew Survival Weapon, issued to U.S. Air Force aircrew from the late 1950s until the early 1970s. Aircrew who were issued the M6 were instructed how to make a field expedient forearm by wrapping the barrels with a length of 550 paracord.  This has been done on this weapon, with the paracord wrapped neatly but carefully so as not to compress the barrels.

Thus is a survival-type gun equipped with a hidden storage compartment along the top of the buttstock to hold extra ammunition (15 rounds of .22 lr, AND 4 rounds of .410), and a grip-type trigger designed for use while wearing a glove, as well as normal finger-operated use.  This gun has a flip-up, interchangeable sight, for use when you are firing either the rifle or shotgun barrel and also has embedded screws for a scope mount. The gun breaks down into two pieces with the removal of one, easy-to-remove, captive pin (a spare pin is also included in this sale).

This model was imported by the Springfield Armory (logo and markings in the right side) and manufactured by Ceská Zbrojovka Uhersky Brod (CZ) (logo and markings in the left side). This model is the .22 LR/.410 shotgun bore combination. The gun is in excellent condition. Both bores are bright and shiny.

This fine firearm breaks down into two sections for easy transport and scratch-free storage in the included, two-compartment, new case which is specially made by Springfield Armory for the M6.  The M6 is designed as a breakdown gun which can easily be carried in a backpack for use as a camp gun on camping or hunting trips.  It also makes a nice truck gun for every-day availability.  

The combination of readily available .22 long rifle and .410 shotgun ammunition for use in one firearm also make it an ideal addition to your emergency planning and survival gear.

Price is FIRM, CASH ONLY Please, NO Trades. This is a private sale so there is no tax. Please note that you must be at least 18 to complete this purchase. Please email me if you are interested or have questions.

PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING SO WE CAN BOTH AVOID LEGAL PROBLEMS!

1. At the time of sale, I will provide two copies of a bill of sale which we will both sign (we each keep a signed copy). The bill of sale will state that you can legally buy and possess a firearm and that you are an Arizona resident. 

I will also provide you with a copy of my current and valid Arizona driver’s license for your records. 

2. At the time of sale, you will need you to provide me with a copy of your current and valid Arizona driver’s license for my records. If you have a current and valid AZ CCW permit, that would be great too.

I look forward to hearing from you and selling you this excellent firearm. Thanks.
